# ==============================================================================
# Notes
# ==============================================================================
#
# Team names used above (update as project grows):
# - @oscura-re/maintainers: Project maintainers (have final say)
# - @oscura-re/core-team: Core library and architecture
# - @oscura-re/automotive-team: Automotive protocols and analysis
# - @oscura-re/protocols-team: Protocol decoders and analyzers
# - @oscura-re/reverse-engineering-team: State machine inference, RE tools
# - @oscura-re/security-team: Security analysis and side-channel
# - @oscura-re/devops-team: CI/CD, build, deployment
# - @oscura-re/release-team: Release management and packaging
# - @oscura-re/qa-team: Testing infrastructure and quality assurance
# - @oscura-re/documentation-team: Documentation and tutorials
#
# Until these teams are created in GitHub, individual usernames can be used.
# Example: /src/oscura/core/ @username1 @username2
#
